children.text: There is a section of plaster that has been installed within 200mm of the edge of the opening, making it susceptible to cracking.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’.
The plasterboard manufacturer requires in their installation manual that
‘Sheet joints are not to coincide with the edge of openings (eg doorways, windows or vents etc).
Sheets are to be laid so that any joint falls a minimum of 200mm from the edge of an opening. Avoid butt joints over single doorways and cavity sliding doors wherever possible. Refer to FIG 10’ .
To avoid future cracking, the builder should replace the plasterboard in this area.
